Careers


Matthews International offers a wide array of opportunities and working environments as diverse as our individual divisions. We recognize that the efforts of employees past and present have made the company what it is today and that employees are vital to our continued success.
Matthews is dedicated to the philosophy of promotion from within. To fulfill this commitment, we hire people who are able to grow in responsibility and capability. To those who meet our high standards, we offer a competitive total compensation and benefit package. Additional information concerning employee benefit programs is available through local management.


Benefits

Benefits are offered to all regular full-time, non-union employees who complete the required eligibility period. Matthews is pleased to offer the following benefits package:

Medical Insurance Coverage
Dental Insurance Coverage
Life Insurance Coverage
Disability Insurance
401K Plan
Paid Vacation Days
Paid Personal Holiday
Paid Holidays
Employee Assistance Program


Travel Accident Insurance
Voluntary Accidental Death and Dismemberment Insurance
Employee Stock Purchase Plan
Service Awards
Educational Assistance
Educational Assistance for Children of Employees
Credit Union


The above applies to U.S. locations only, and benefit packages vary by location.


EEO Statement

All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin or protected veteran status and will not be discriminated against on the basis of disability.





